column1:
Note:
This extension is compatible with Preload Critical Resources + Assets
This extensions allows to improve your Core Web Vitals page experience KPIs even further by using Resource Hints for Preload Critical Resources & Assets incl. Improved Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) images.
For LCP images the best available image format will be preloaded automatically (WebP, AVIF, High-Res).
For more details please see the Manual.

Note:

column1:
Exclude images from AVIF/WebP Conversion by a list of comma separated RegEx.
If the img tag match with any of the RegEx above,
that img tag won't be converted.
Note: img-tags with data-nowebp="true", data-noavif="true" and in media/captcha folder are excluded from conversion by default.
column2:
Exclude images from AVIF/WebP Conversion by a list of comma separated RegEx.
If the img tag match with any of the RegEx above,
that img tag won't be converted.
Note: img-tags with data-nowebp="true", data-noavif="true" and in media/captcha folder are excluded from conversion by default.

column1:
By default we look at the src attribute to get the image URL and use this for AVIF/WebP conversion and applying image optimizations.
If you use some custom attribute for img URL, e. g. in case you are using lazyload on your site, you can use this config to have this converted first.
Example: If your lazy load function uses data-src, just input data-src into this config.
For img tags having a data-src we will then use the data-src image URL for AVIF/WebP conversion and applying image optimizations.
For img tags having no data-src, we will still use src attribute for conversion.
column2:
By default we look at the src attribute to get the image URL and use this for AVIF/WebP conversion and applying image optimizations.
If you use some custom attribute for img URL, e. g. in case you are using lazyload on your site, you can use this config to have this converted first.
Example: If your lazy load function uses data-src, just input data-src into this config.
For img tags having a data-src we will then use the data-src image URL for AVIF/WebP conversion and applying image optimizations.
For img tags having no data-src, we will still use src attribute for conversion.

column1:
By default we add picture tags using srcset tags.
You can use this config to change this behaviour, e. g. in case you are using lazy load on your site.
Example: If your lazy load function uses data-srcset, just input data-srcset into this config.
The extension will then add picture/source tags using data-srcset.
!!! Please ensure your lazy load script does support lazy loading for picture-tags !!!
column2:

!!! Please ensure your lazy load script does support lazy loading for picture-tags !!!

column1:
By clicking on Allow, you agree that we may collect anonymous usage data from you to:

  1. Help us improve the Magento Admin user experience
  2. Provide interactive in-product guidance, such as technical support and tips to improve utilization of the product from within the Admin UI. This may include notifications of new features, product support/guidance, onboarding information, tooltips, and more.

All usage data that we collect for this purpose cannot be used to individually identify you and is used only to improve the Magento Admin UI and related products and services.

You can learn more and opt-out at any time by following the instructions in merchant documentation.

column1:
Parallax Speed controls how the background will behave when page is scrolled.

Negative values will make the background scroll in the reverse direction.

Values from 0 to 1 will cause the scroll to be slower than the scroll speed of the window, values from 1 to 2 will be faster.

0 - Fixes the background to the window (e.g. no scrolling).

1 - Background will scroll at the same speed as the window.
